highlights.title: United States-Los Angeles, California
highlights.subtitle: United States-Los Angeles, California
highlights.excerpt: Grammy week in Los Angeles is a time when the world comes together to celebrate the most creative and inspiring efforts of top musicians over the last year. This year, the Grammy Foundation and Audigy Group decided to also help give some children and adults in need the opportunity to enjoy music like never before by partnering with us to give them the gift of hearing.

highlights.title: Senegal-Dakar
highlights.subtitle: Senegal-Dakar
highlights.excerpt: The gift of hearing gave new life to Senegal's explosive colors and brilliant smiles during this hearing mission in Dakar. Famous Senegalese musician Walley Ballago Seck soothed the nerves of more than 1,500 patients as the team fit them with hearing aids.

highlights.title: Ghana-Accra
highlights.subtitle: Ghana-Accra
highlights.excerpt: The road we travel is always filled with friends, and during our hearing mission in Ghana we were thrilled to welcome the support of so many. From 1 to 81, patients arrived with hopeful eyes as the team and our local partners gave more than 1,900 children and adults a new connection to life.

highlights.title: Haiti-Port-au-Prince, Saint Marc
highlights.subtitle: Haiti-Port-au-Prince, Saint Marc
highlights.excerpt: Decimated by catastrophic magnitude 7.0 earthquake in 2010, Haiti has struggled to rebuild an infrastructure and economy that was already the poorest in the Western Hemisphere. Even with all the humanitarian aid that has poured into the country, the need across all of society has made it difficult to reach those living with hearing loss. Focusing specifically on schools for the deaf, the hearing mission team, joined by partners Clinton Global Initiative and Hope to Haiti and volunteer former Los Angeles Galaxy player Tony Sanneh, gave the gift of hearing students.

highlights.title: United States-New York City, New York
highlights.subtitle: United States-New York City, New York
highlights.excerpt: Seattle Seahawk Derrick Coleman took time the day before the Super Bowl to fit New Yorkers in need with hearing aids. Coleman, along with Garth Brooks, Joe Girardi, Larry Fitzgerald, A.J. Green, Tommie Harris, Andre Roberts, Daymond John, Barbara Bush and a host of other celebrities and pro athletes, attended our annual Super Bowl hearing mission, hosted this year by the New York Yankees. After receiving a hero’s welcome from children inspired by his story, the running back helped give patients the gift of hearing. Excited to help Coleman prepare for the biggest game of his life, the hearing mission team made sure his Starkey hearing aids were in perfect working order to help lead him to victory.

highlights.title: Liberia-Monrovia
highlights.subtitle: Liberia-Monrovia
highlights.excerpt: The first female head of state in Africa and Nobel Prize winner Liberian President Ellen Johnson Sirleaf joined the team in Monrovia to highlight the importance of hearing care. We worked diligently to ensure more than 300 patients were given a deeper connection to the world of sound.

highlights.title: Dominican Republic-Santo Domingo, Santiago
highlights.subtitle: Dominican Republic-Santo Domingo, Santiago
highlights.excerpt: Excited to be back in the land of merengue, the team went directly to work opening up the world of sound, music and dance to children and adults in a culture defined by rhythm. Baseball Hall of Famer Paul Molitor and dedicated partner FedEx joined the team to help give the gift of hearing to more than 1,700 patients.
